ce:section.ce:para:
Ti–Si–N ternary system includes the following phases:

-

the gas phase;


-

the liquid solution phase;


-

the diamond-Si phase, denoted Si;


-

the ternary solution phases: (βTi), the solution of N and Si in bcc Ti; (αTi), the solution of N and Si in hcp Ti; TiN, the solution of N and Si in fcc Ti; and Ti5Si3N
x
, the ternary extension of the binary phase Ti5Si3;


-

the stoichiometric compound phases: Ti3Si, Ti5Si4, TiSi, TiSi2, Si3N4 and Ti2N.
